I took my wife to this show expecting to see some great illusions with a touch of Cirque. Instead we witnessed a handful of Mindfreak clips which can be seen for free via youtube and 12 versions of the disappear then reappear somewhere else act. As we left the theater I seriously thought about locating a police officer to report a robbery. I must admit that Criss Angel did a wonderful job of making my money disappear.   If you are set on seeing a show in Vegas I would suggest anything but this. Better yet, take the $100 you would have paid per ticket and give it to one of the homeless people you see on the bridges or place a healthy bet on one of the roulette tables. Either way you have a much better shot at feeling good about yourself then you would after leaving this show.

